Author: iampieman
Text: Thank-you. Part of me knows this, but a louder part of me just screams about how this is failing. But thanks for the comment, I appreciate it!

Author: Lunaseki
Text: The goal posts always get moved. 500 is objectively a low number to eat at, but when you eat at 300 for a couple days, suddenly 500 seems like a failure. It’s so upsetting and I’m sorry you’re dealing with this... just remember that by all means, you’re eating a very small number of calories. It won’t make the difference you feel like it will.
